<h2>Link Building for Cleaning Companies</h2>
<p>Backlinks remain a top ranking factor. For cleaning companies, the best links come from local and industry-specific sources.</p>
<h3>Local Link Opportunities</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Chamber of Commerce</strong> membership (most include a website link)</li>
<li><strong>Local sponsorships</strong>. School events, charity drives, community clean-up days</li>
<li><strong>Real estate agent partnerships</strong>. Agents need move-in/out cleaning referrals. Offer a referral program and ask for a link on their "preferred vendors" page.</li>
<li><strong>Property management companies</strong>. Similar referral opportunity with a link exchange</li>
<li><strong>Local news and blogs</strong>. Offer cleaning tips for seasonal articles. Local lifestyle blogs love "spring cleaning" content.</li>
<li><strong>Airbnb host communities</strong>. Many Airbnb forums and local host groups link to recommended cleaning services</li>
</ul>
<h3>Industry-Specific Links</h3>
<ul>
<li>Cleaning trade associations (ISSA, ARCSI)</li>
<li>Franchise directories (if applicable)</li>
