<h2>FAQ</h2>
<p><strong>How much does SEO cost for a cleaning company?</strong></p>
<p>DIY SEO costs $0 to $300 per month in tools. A freelancer or small agency charges $500 to $2,000 per month. Full-service SEO agencies charge $2,000 to $5,000 per month. Stacc offers blog SEO starting at $99 per month and local SEO starting at $49 per month, covering content publishing and GBP management.</p>
<p><strong>How long does SEO take for a cleaning business?</strong></p>
<p>Expect initial ranking movement within 60 to 90 days. Consistent lead flow typically starts around month 5 to 6. Full market dominance takes 12+ months of sustained work. Competition level and market size affect the timeline. Read our guide on <a href="/blog/how-long-seo-takes/">how long SEO takes</a> for detailed breakdowns.</p>
<p><strong>Is SEO or Google Ads better for cleaning companies?</strong></p>
<p>Both serve different roles. Google Ads delivers leads immediately but costs $15 to $40 per click for cleaning keywords. SEO compounds over time and delivers lower cost per lead after the initial ramp-up. Most successful cleaning companies run both. Use Ads for immediate revenue while SEO builds momentum.</p>
<p><strong>What are the best keywords for cleaning companies?</strong></p>
<p>Start with high-intent local keywords: "house cleaning [city]," "maid service near me," and "deep cleaning [city]." Then target informational keywords like "house cleaning cost," "deep cleaning checklist," and "how often to deep clean." Local keywords with your city name convert best because they match high-intent searches.</p>
<p><strong>Do cleaning companies need a blog?</strong></p>
<p>Yes. Blog content drives organic traffic, builds authority, and creates internal links to your service pages. Cleaning companies that publish 4+ posts per month rank for 3x more keywords than those with static websites. Each post creates another opportunity to appear in Google and AI search results.</p>
<p><strong>How do I get more reviews for my cleaning company?</strong></p>
<p>Send a text message with a direct Google review link within 2 hours of completing a cleaning job. Include a QR code on your leave-behind card. Follow up once 3 days later. Respond to every review publicly. Target 2 to 4 new reviews per month. See our full guide on <a href="/blog/get-more-google-reviews-local-business/">getting more Google reviews</a>.</p>
<p>SEO for cleaning companies is not optional in 2026. The companies booking the most jobs are the ones showing up first when homeowners search. Every month you wait is another month your competitors build their organic presence while yours stays invisible. Start with your Google Business Profile, create your service pages, and publish content every week. The bookings follow.</p>
